The paper is about open problems in computational geometry, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with algorithms and data structures for geometric problems. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The problems presented also involve topics such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT), which are all relevant to computational geometry.
